The ProgramManager provides the functional unit's program manager.

The ActiveProgram specifies the current state of operation of a FunctionalUnit. It provides context and information about the currently active program on the device. This allows users to follow the progress of a program run in a standardized fashion by organising steps into a flat, linear sequence.

UAVariable.Description: CurrentProgramTemplate provides the template-id as well as the node-id of the currently executed program.

CurrentRuntime is the current run-time of the program -run. The CurrentRunTime is set to 0 at the start of the program and is counted upwards as long as the program run is not in a Paused state. The Paused state is an aggregation of the Suspended state and the Held state.
CurrentStepName is the name of the current step.
CurrentStepNumber is the number/index of the current step (incremented whenever the next step is entered). The CurrentStepNumber starts with 1.

CurrentStepRuntime is the runtime of the current step. The CurrentStepRunTime is set to 0 at the start of the current step and is counted upwards as long as the program run is not in Paused state. The Paused state is an aggregation of the Suspended state and the Held State.
EstimatedRuntime is the estimated run-time of the current program run. If the runtime cannot be estimated, the StatusCode BadNoData should be sent.
EstimatedStepNumbers are the estimated total number of steps of the current program run. If the total number cannot be estimated, the StatusCode BadNoData should be sent.
EstimatedStepRuntime is the estimated run-time of the current program-step. If the run-time cannot estimate, the StatusCode BadNoData should sent.
